Atomic RMI
==========

Overview
--------

The archive contains the following:

 - Atomic RMI binaries:
    * dist/atomicrmi-all-0.2.jar
    * bin/

 - libraries necessary to run Atomic RMI:
    * lib/cglib-nodep-2.2.jar  

 - libraries necessary to run the Atomic RMI Precompiler:
    * lib/jasminclasses-2.4.0.jar  
    * lib/polyglot-1.3.3.jar  
    * lib/sootclasses-2.4.0.jar

 - examples
    * test/
 
 - scripts for running the examples:
    * scripts/server.sh
    * scripts/client_audit.sh
    * scripts/client_transfer.sh
    * scripts/client_transfer_retry.sh

Running the examples
--------------------

  The example consists of a server and clients that communicate with it. 

  They all take two commandline arguments:
    * the name of the host where RMI registry is running
    * the port of RMI registry

  First, start the server: 
    scripts/server.sh localhost 1099

  Then, in another terminal start either of the clients:
    scripts/client_audit.sh localhost 1099
    scripts/client_transfer.sh localhost 1099
    scripts/client_transfer_retry.sh localhost 1099

  Starting the precompiler:
    scripts/precompiler.sh --sources=<DIRECTORY> --classes=<DIRECTORY> <CLASSNAME>

